 Software Requirements

Operating System:
Linux or Ubuntu (any recent version)
Windows (with WSL â€“ Windows Subsystem for Linux) can work too
Compiler:
GCC (GNU Compiler Collection)
Libraries:
libpcap (Packet capture library)
Install with:
         sudo apt update
         sudo apt install libpcap-dev

 Terminal/Shell:

A terminal to run the shell interface ($ prompt)
Ability to run sudo commands for capturing packets

 Hardware Requirements

Any PC or laptop with network interface (Ethernet/Wi-Fi)
Internet connection (optional, but real packets require network activity)

 Optional Tools

Text editor: nano, vim, or VS Code
Git (if pushing to GitHub)
     Summary

To run the project successfully, make sure you have:
Linux system

GCC compiler installed
libpcap-dev installed
Network interface active
Then you can compile and run:
     gcc vishal_sniffer.c -lpcap -o vishal_sniffer
     sudo ./vishal_sniffer
